                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. F.W.462.11T41</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1471. American citizen reported drowned when British steamship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Falaba</hi> was sunk March 28 by German submarine. Has there been <pb
                        facs="0617" n="359" xml:id="pg_359"/> official report of incident? If not,
                    can you obtain by discreet and unofficial inquiries German account, and
                    particularly reason for torpedoing <hi rend="italic">Falaba</hi> before crew and
                    passengers had time to withdraw in boats to a distance from vessel sufficient to
                    insure safety when <hi rend="italic">Falaba</hi> sank? You are urgently
                    requested to report as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
